The paper deals with visual recognition and retrieval of objects from large databases, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses statistical hypothesis testing, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves learning from a single sequence for each known gallery object, which is a common technique in transfer learning (cs.LG).
